:R-HSA-2408550  a           obo:GO_0001887 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Ingested selenic acid (H2SeO4) and selenite (SeO3(2-)) are reduced to hydrogen selenide (H2Se) through a combination of actions involving bifunctional 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate synthase 1 and 2 (PAPSS1/2), PAPSe reductase (PAPSeR), and thioredoxin reductase 1 (TXNRD1)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Metabolism of ingested H2SeO4 and H2SeO3 into H2Se" ;
